Car Price Prediction using Machine Learning
1. Introduction

Car price prediction is an important application of Machine Learning that helps estimate the selling price of a used car based on its features. In this project, a Linear Regression model was developed to predict car prices using historical data. The project demonstrates the complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, visualization, model training, and performance evaluation.

2. Objective

The main objectives of this project are:

To analyze the car dataset.
To clean and preprocess the data.
To visualize important relationships between variables.
To build a Linear Regression model for predicting car prices.
To evaluate the model using different performance metrics.
3. Dataset Description

The dataset contains information about different cars and their selling prices.

Dataset Details
Total Records: 301
Records after removing duplicates: 299
Total Features: 9
Features Used
Car_Name
Year
Selling_Price (Target Variable)
Present_Price
Driven_kms
Fuel_Type
Selling_type
Transmission
Owner
4. Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

Loaded the dataset using Pandas.
Checked missing values.
No missing values were found.
Removed duplicate records.
Encoded categorical variables using LabelEncoder.
Prepared feature and target variables for machine learning.
5. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Several visualizations were created to better understand the dataset.

Selling Price Distribution

The histogram shows the distribution of car selling prices. Most vehicles fall into the lower price range, while only a few cars have very high selling prices.

